    "ts": "2026-05-18T06:34:40+00:00",
    "headline": "Indian court tells Apple to 'cooperate' in antitrust case",
    "summary": "An Indian court has told Apple to \"fully cooperate\" with investigators in an ‌antitrust case related to the iPhone apps market, not ‌agreeing with the U.S. company's request to put the case on hold ​while it challenges the law governing antitrust penalties.  • The Delhi High Court said in an order posted on its website on Saturday that Apple \"shall fully cooperate\", but it asked the ‌Competition Commission of India (CCI) ⁠to not pass a final order in the matter until at least July 15.  • Apple wanted ⁠the case to be put on hold and had accused the CCI of exceeding its powers by pushing the company ​to submit ​its financials - typically needed for ​penalty calculation - while Apple ‌has a pending challenge to the law governing penalties, Reuters has reported.",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/indian-court-tells-apple-cooperate-063440210.html",
    "source": "Reuters",
    "provider": "yfinance",
    "raw": {
      "id": "26988a93-a96a-3cc1-a070-cbb27cf363ce",
      "content": {
        "id": "26988a93-a96a-3cc1-a070-cbb27cf363ce",
        "contentType": "STORY",
        "title": "Indian court tells Apple to 'cooperate' in antitrust case",
        "description": "",
        "summary": "An Indian court has told Apple to \"fully cooperate\" with investigators in an ‌antitrust case related to the iPhone apps market, not ‌agreeing with the U.S. company's request to put the case on hold ​while it challenges the law governing antitrust penalties.  • The Delhi High Court said in an order posted on its website on Saturday that Apple \"shall fully cooperate\", but it asked the ‌Competition Commission of India (CCI) ⁠to not pass a final order in the matter until at least July 15.  • Apple wanted ⁠the case to be put on hold and had accused the CCI of exceeding its powers by pushing the company ​to submit ​its financials - typically needed for ​penalty calculation - while Apple ‌has a pending challenge to the law governing penalties, Reuters has reported.",
